Pi'el: The "pi'el" (פִּעֵל) is one of the [[Hebrew binyanim]]. ([[{{Binyan}} is a special grammatical construct in Hebrew and Aramaic]].) Verbs in the _hif'il_ have the properties of being [[active]] and [[intensive]]. The _pi'el_ corresponds to the [[_pa'el_]] in Aramaic.

- * Pi'el participle: The _pi'el_ participle tense is the [[participle tense]] of the [[{{_pi'el_}} binyan]]. The _pi'el participle_ is usually formed by adding a מ to the beginning of the shoresh, like מְקַדֵּשׁ for the shoresh קדש.
